This paper discusses scheduling mechanisms and throughput optimization for IEEE 802.11ax and IEEE 802.11ac networks, which are both related to computer networks and communication systems (cs.NI). The paper also explores modulation and coding schemes (cs.IT), multiple-input-multiple-output (MIMO) and orthogonal frequency division multiple access (OFDMA) transmission multiplexing format (cs.MM), and acknowledges operation settings (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the networks in terms of access delay (cs.AR).
